  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis power-law coefficients and damage accumulation methodology follow the framework described in the peer-reviewed validation study indexed at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003, which provides the empirical basis for the relative hemolysis index (RH) acceptance criterion used throughout this assessment.",
